This paper discusses the economic analysis of Bitcoin transaction channels, specifically the lightning network, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the impact of transaction channels on the network topology and demand for transactions, which could fall under the categories of graph theory (cs.GT) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the impact of transaction channels on network infrastructure, which could fall under the categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
